$lang['Hexadecimal numbers are made up of 16 digits instead of the 10 in a decimal number. The order of these numbers starts over after F (or 15 in decimal), while it doesn’t in the decimals. Check out the table below to see how they compare!'] = 'Ọnụọgụ hexadecimal bụ ọnụọgụ iri na isii kama nke iri n&#39;ọnụọgụ iri. Usoro nke ọnụọgụgụ ndị a na-amalite mgbe F (ma ọ bụ 15 na decimal), ebe ọ na-adịghị na decimal. Lelee tebụl dị n&#39;okpuru ka ịhụ ka ha si atụnyere!';
