$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal bụ ụzọ na-anọchi anya ọnụọgụ abụọ n&#39;ụdị mmadụ nwere ike ịgụ. E mepụtara ya na narị afọ nke 19 iji kwe ka kọmputa na-echekwa ozi buru ibu.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Ị nwere ike iji hexadecimal tụgharịa n&#39;etiti ọnụọgụ iri na ọnụọgụ abụọ. Dịka ọmụmaatụ, ịtụgharị 10011011001010 ka ọ bụrụ hexadecimal ga-ebute 0x4F. Nke a pụtara na uru 4F na-anọchi anya ọnụọgụ ọnụọgụ abụọ 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Na mgbakọ na mwepụ na sayensị kọmputa, hexadecimal (nakwa ntọala 16, ma ọ bụ hex) bụ usoro ọnụọgụ ọnọdụ nwere radix, ma ọ bụ isi, nke 16. Ọ na-eji akara iri na isii dị iche iche, ọtụtụ mgbe akara 0-9 na-anọchi anya ụkpụrụ efu na itoolu. na A, B, C, D, E, F (ma ọ bụ ọzọ a–f) iji nọchite anya ụkpụrụ iri ruo iri na ise. Dịka ọmụmaatụ, ọnụọgụ hexadecimal 2AF3 hà nhata, na ngụkọ, na (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , ma ọ bụ 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Ọnụọgụ hexadecimal ọ bụla na-anọchi anya ọnụọgụ ọnụọgụ abụọ (bits) anọ (nke a na-akpọkwa &quot;nibble&quot;), na isi ojiji e ji akara hexadecimal bụ ihe nnochite anya enyi mmadụ nke ụkpụrụ ọnụọgụ abụọ koodu na kọmpụta na elektrọnik dijitalụ. Dịka ọmụmaatụ, ụkpụrụ byte nwere ike ịdị na 0 ruo 255 (ngụkọta ọnụ ọgụgụ) mana enwere ike gosipụta ya nke ọma dị ka ọnụọgụ hexadecimal abụọ na nso 00 ruo FF. A na-ejikwa hexadecimal na-anọchi anya adreesị ebe nchekwa kọmputa.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex bụ mbiri nke Hexadecimal, nke dabere na ntọala -16 ma jiri ya mee ka ọ dị mfe ka esi egosipụta ntuziaka na kọmpụta. Emepụtara sistemu akara akara iri na isii a ka ụzọ isi gbochie ọnụọgụ ọnụọgụ abụọ 8-bit, yabụ enwere ike itinye data n&#39;ime kọmpụta n&#39;enweghị ike. Enwere ike bipụta ya wee pịnye ya site na iji ọnụọgụ hex abụọ dị iche iche yana mkpụrụ ọnụọgụ hex ọ bụla na-egosipụta nibble ma ọ bụ ikekwe usoro 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sistemu ọnụọgụgụ a na-eji akara 16 nọchitere anya na nso 0-9 ma ọ bụ AF. 0–9 na-anọchi anya ọnụọgụ ruru itoolu ebe ọnụọgụ 10–15 nọchiri anya AF. Dịka atụnyere ụdị usoro ọnụọgụ atọ ndị ọzọ, a na-ewere usoro ọnụọgụ hexadecimal ka ọ kacha dị irè.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Koodu hexadecimal gị ezighi ezi';
